      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(google): remove stale -preview suffix from gemini-3.1-flash-lite model ID",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nGoogle graduated `gemini-3.1-flash-lite` from preview to GA on May 7, 2026. The `-preview` endpoint is scheduled for shutdown on May 25, 2026. However, the codebase still rewrites `gemini-3.1-flash-lite` to `gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview` in multiple normalization surfaces, actively routing users to the deprecated endpoint.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Remove `gemini-3.1-flash-lite` → `gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview` rewrite from `extensions/google/model-id.ts` and `src/plugin-sdk/provider-model-id-normalize.ts`\n- Remove stale alias entries from `extensions/google/openclaw.plugin.json` (google, google-gemini-cli, google-vertex providers)\n- Update default model alias in `src/config/defaults.ts`\n- Update template ID in `extensions/google/provider-models.ts` and CLI backend alias in `extensions/google/cli-backend.ts`\n- Update test expectations in `model-id.test.ts`, `model-selection.test.ts`, `model-alias-defaults.test.ts`, and `gateway-models.profiles.live.test.ts`\n\n## Testing\n\n- Verified all normalization surfaces updated consistently\n- Backwards compatibility: `shouldSkipExecReadNonceMissForLiveModel` test still accepts both `-preview` and non-preview IDs\n- Note: some test fixtures in other files still reference the old `-preview` ID for unrelated tests (billing, auth, image). These can be updated separately.\n- Relying on CI for full test suite execution\n\nCloses #86151",
        "branch": "fix/issue-86151-gemini-flash-lite-preview",
